The tribesman have been waging months-long rebellion in bid to win increased royalties, more jobs from province's natural resources.
Interior Minister Aftab Sherpao said tribesmen used light, heavy weapons, rained more than 150 rockets, mortar shells on nearby paramilitary base from 12 different directions.
Also late Saturday 39 devotees were killed, scores injured in powerful bomb blast at memorial of Muslim Sufi saint in remote town of Fatahpur.
Baluchistan has been gripped by sporadic tribal revolt for more than year but violence surged after January rape of a 32 year-old doctor at Pakistan's largest gas field at Sui.
